Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a video model that estimates the joint distribution of raw pixel values in a video. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a neural architecture for the model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a probabilistic model for video generation. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper proposes a neural architecture for the model. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper evaluates the model on a robotic pushing benchmark and generalizes to the motion of novel objects.
